campAnduin = "Down the Anduin",
campAnduinInfo = "You leave Mirkwood with a message from King Thranduil to Lady Galadriel. Your plan to raft down the Anduin River south is thwarted.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Wood Elves\nRegion: Anduin, Dol Guldur",
campAruwethil = "The Undercity",
campAruwethilInfo = "[i]You stopped the hillmen's ritual and destroyed the horrific contraption. But the mysterious woman must still be somewhere. You suspect the danger she poses and decide to track her down in the city beneath Fornost's ruins and to may the hunt begin![/i]\n\nDifficulty: Hard\nRecommended Characters: Hobbits, Dúnedain\nRegion: Fornost",
campBarrowDowns = "The Barrow Downs",
campBarrowDownsInfo = "Your research has revealed that there is a larger story behind the turmoil in Bree. You follow a lead into the infamous Barrow Downs. In the dense fog you look for further signs of evil machinations\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Dúnedain\nRegion: Eriador, Barrow Riss",
campBreeMurder = "Murder and Manslaughter",
campBreeMurderInfo = "A horrifying murder is shaking the peaceful village of Bree. Who could be behind this heinous act…and what is the motive?\n\nDifficulty: Easy\nRecommended Characters: Hobbits, Dúnedain\nRegion: Bree ",
campBreeTrouble = "Trouble in Bree",
campBreeTroubleInfo = "There is great excitement in Bree. Bandits lurk in the shadows, robbing with impunity. The fearful residents eagerly await someone to rescue them from the rabble.\n\nDifficulty: Easy\nRecommended characters: Dunedain\nRegion: Bree",
campCairAndros = "Siege of Cair Andros",
campCairAndrosInfo = "[i]In Ithilien you have received an urgent message: The enemy has massed troops and is attempting to attack Cair Andros. The fortified island in Anduin serves as Gondor's bulwark against the danger from the east and must not fall into enemy hands under any circumstances You immediately decide to rush to the aid of the defenders of Gondor with your companions.[/i]\n\nDifficulty: Hard\nRecommended Characters: Gondor\nRegion: Cair Andros",
campCarnDum = "The Dread Realm of Carn Dûm",
campCarnDumInfo = "You have successfully made it back to Rivendell, where Elrond is about to have a briefing held. There is no doubt that evil has grown strong in the north and wants to breathe new, corrupted life into the legacy of Angmar. Only determined action can do that prevent Angmar from awakening again.\nThere is much evidence that the source of the increased enemy power lies within the fortress of Carn Dûm, once the seat of the witch-king of Angmar.While Aragorn summons the ready-to-fight Dúnedain to Rivendell, Elrond gathers a small army Hopefully, by joining forces it will be possible to drive the corruption back out of Eriador.\n\nDifficulty: Hard\nRecommended Characters: Dúnedain, Noldor\nRegion: Carn Dûm",
campCarrock = "Across the High Pass",
campCarrockInfo = "You set off from Rivendell with your group of traveling companions to visit Beorn on the other side of the Misty Mountains. On the way you are soon surprised by wintry weather. Orcs and wolves scent fresh air as you struggle through the snow Loot.\n\nDifficulty: Hard\nRecommended Characters: Noldor\nRegion: Misty Mountains",
campChetwald = "Bree-land in danger",
campChetwaldInfo = "You are resting from your adventures in the House of Elrond when a messenger for Aragorn arrives. The Dúnedain reports of a large band of Orcs being observed west of the Weathermounts.\n'We haven't seen that many this far to the west for a long time. They scout the land and we fear they may raid the settlements of Bree-land.\nYou glance at your companions and see determined faces. 'It seems the time of rest is over. We will stand with the Dúnedain and keep the Orcs out of Bree-land.'\nThe same day you set out west.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Dúnedain\nRegion: Chetwood, Weather Hills",
campConspiracy = "Conspiracy in Minas Tirith",
campConspiracyInfo = "[i]At the invitation of the Steward of Gondor, you and your fellowship arrive in Minas Tirith, the White City. You learn that the governor is concerned about suspicious activity in the city. Yet Gondor has enough enemies outside the city walls. You agree to investigate a possible conspiracy.[/i]\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Gondor\nRegion: Minas Tirith",
campDefeat = "You failed because you could not complete the campaign tasks.",
campDolGuldur = "Inspection of Dol Guldur",
campDolGuldurInfo = "After your journey through Mirkwood, one thing is certain: dark things are happening around the ancient fortress of Dol Guldur. After some deliberation, the Lady Galadriel asks you to investigate the dark fortress and find out what or who is there up to mischief.\n\nDifficulty: medium\nRecommended characters: any\nRegion: Mirkwood, Dol Guldur",
campDruadan = "Through the Drúadan Forest",
campDruadanInfo = "After the expensive but successful defense of Cair Andros, it's now a matter of hunting down the scattered enemies. You follow a horde of Orcs that are moving westwards into Gondor's interior. You must stop them before they can attack the hinterland. But when their trail finally leads into the Drúadan Forest, you have doubts...\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Gondor\nRegion: Drúadan Forest",
campDunlandperlen = "No Free Trade in Dunland",
campDunlandperlenInfo = "On your way from Rohan to Rivendell, you encounter a desperate woman on a lonely road. Her eyes are reddened with tears, and her voice is filled with fear as she tells you about her plight. Her husband, a wealthy merchant, has been captured by the Dunlanders. She begs you to rescue him and bring him safely back to her.\n\nYou learn that the merchant was captured by the Dunlanders during a raid on his trade route. The conflict between the Dunlanders and the Rohirrim is tense, and the dangerous routes are full of enemies. Your help is urgently needed, as the merchant is held in a secret camp deep within Dunland.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Rohirrim\nRegion: Dunland",
campDunlandwolves = "The Blood Pact",
campDunlandwolvesInfo = "News of your escape from Dunland has enraged the Wolf Clan. Now the Dunlendings swarm towards the Fords of Isen, determined to breach the way into Rohan. You must stand against them, side by side with the brave Rohirrim, to halt the flood of these savage warriors. The defense of the Fords is crucial, for if they fall, the path to Rohan will be wide open. You know you must hold out until reinforcements arrive—or until the last enemy is defeated. As you prepare for the defense, a dreadful howling fills the air. It seems the Wolf Clan has forged a pact with the Wargs of the Misty Mountains.\n\nDifficulty = Hard\nRecommended Characters = Rohirrim\nRegion = Rohan, Dunland",
campDurinsBane = "Durin's Bane",
campDurinsBaneInfo = "You have ventured into the eastern mines of Moria and are looking for the exit. Little do you know that far more terrible things await you in the depths than hordes of orcs.\n\nDifficulty: Hard\nRecommended Characters: Dwarves\nRegion: Moria",
campEdoras = "The King's Arms",
campEdorasInfo = "You have just arrived in Edoras to offer your services to the king of Rohan when a riot breaks out in the city. Apparently the armory has been broken into and among the stolen weapons is said to be the royal sword Herugrim. No one would trust a local to commit such a brazen crime, so suspicion falls on you. You could not have arrived at a worse time, but at least the king is not convinced of your guilt. To save your own skin, you promise to by help solve the theft.\n\nDifficulty: Easy\nRecommended Characters: Rohan\nRegion: Rohan, Edoras",
campErebor = "The Heart of Erebor",
campEreborInfo = "After years of peace and reconstruction in Erebor under King Dáin Ironfoot, the dwarven kingdom is flourishing once again. Yet deep within the Lonely Mountain, strange noises and missing workers have stirred unease. Rumors of ancient creatures lurking in the forgotten depths spread fear among the miners. The king calls upon brave adventurers to lead an expedition into the unexplored depths, secure the newly opened mines, and uncover what ancient threats have resurfaced. It is your task to heed the call and rid Erebor of the dark creatures lurking below.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Dwarves\nRegion: Erebor",
campEscapeDolGuldur = "Escape from Dol Guldur",
campEscapeDolGuldurInfo = "In Dol Guldur, your party fell into a trap and was taken to a torture chamber dripping inside the fortress. Try to escape and find a way out of the fortress.\n\nDifficulty: Hard\nRecommended Characters: Any\nRegion: Dol Guldur",
campEttenmoors = "Into the Ettenmoors",
campEttenmoorsInfo = "You and your party have escaped captivity in Mount Gram. You managed to shake off your pursuers, but now you face the arduous journey through the wilds of the Ettenmoors. Orcs, wargs, wildmen, and trolls roam there around and it will be difficult to get to Rivendell unseen.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Any\nRegion: Ettenmoors",
campFangorn = "Into Fangorn",
campFangornInfo = "The orc army in the wastelands has been crushed, but the remnants of the force are fleeing the deadly lances of the Rohirrim. You pursue a group of fleeing orcs towards the northwest, where madness drives them into the Fangorn. You hesitate for a moment, then take give chase.\n\nDifficulty: Hard\nRecommended characters: Ents\nRegion: Fangorn",
campFornost = "No silence in Fornost",
campFornostInfo = "[i]In the notes of the grave robbers at the Barrow Riss you have found a hint that their actual client is in Fornost and is working on secret machinations there. So you head north on the road to Fornost Erain, in the Shire and from the Bree people also known as the Dead Dike. Your party is led by Beravor, who knows the area like no other.[/i]\n\nDifficulty: Hard\nRecommended characters: Hobbits, Dúnedain\nRegion: Fornost",
campFoundationsOfStone = "Foundations of Stone",
campFoundationsOfStoneInfo = "You got lost in the depths of Moria while fleeing the orcs. Not knowing which way leads back to daylight, you follow the dull murmur of an underground river, hoping it will lead you to the exit. \n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Dwarves, Noldor\nRegion: Moria",
campFramsburg = "The Ghost of Framsburg",
campFramsburgInfo = "Framsburg was once a city of the Éothéod, as the Rohirrim were called, before they moved to what is now Rohan. Beorn tells you about the legend of how their namesake, Fram, slew the dragon Scatha rest in a crypt beneath the city. However, Framsburg has been in ruins for hundreds of years. You have a burning thirst for adventure, so you decide on the daring quest to recover the Sword of Fram.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended characters: Thal\nRegion: Framsburg",
campGollum = "The Hunt for Gollum",
campGollumInfo = "You are sitting with Beorn in the great hall, telling each other stories from the old days, when suddenly there is a knock at the door. As you open it, you see a bearded man with a gray coat and a pointed hat. You ask, amazed, what Gandalf the Gray has led to this area of all times.\n'The creature Gollum,' replied the wizard, explaining that the creature had been sighted in the area and that he would be only too happy to speak with it your companions and immediately offer to help.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Dúnedain\nRegion: Mirkwood",
campGram = "Escape from Mount Gram",
campGramInfo = "After fleeing the wolves, you were exhausted and drained. So you couldn't put up a fight when you encountered another group of orcs.\n\nYour luck in misfortune: Like the innocent civilians before, you weren't killed by the orcs, but instead bound and dragged away. A long march in chains brought you to the dungeons of Mount Gram. There you now, each in your own cell, await the threatening doom. If anything, your only hope was with Amarthiúl, who distracted the wolves and therefore didn't run into the arms of the orcs with you.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Dúnedain\nRegion: Mount Gram",
campIthilien = "Mission in Ithilien",
campIthilienInfo = "[i]After you have uncovered and eliminated the conspiracy in Minas Tirith, the steward informs you about the threat on the outer borders of the country. Corsairs threaten the south coast and drive through the mouth of the Anduin to Pelargir, orc squads are in the seen around Cair Andros to the north, and Sauron's allies from the south are moving through Ithilien to Mordor.[/i]\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Gondor, Dúnedain\nRegion: Ithilien",
campKidnapping = "The kidnapping",
campKidnappingInfo = "You are visiting Beorn and enjoying his courteous inn with your friends. However, in the morning after a night of drinking and drinking honey mead, you make a disturbing discovery: one of your companions has disappeared without a trace! What happened? Nobody noticed anything On top of that, Beorn isn't home either, so you must set off to find your companion again.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Any\nRegion: Beorn's Hall, Mirkwood",
campLongDark = "The Long Dark",
campLongDarkInfo = "Your party decides to explore the mines of Moria. First you must find the dwarven door and speak the password. Beyond that lies a deep darkness and branching passages that you can wander endlessly through if you take a wrong turn.\n\nDifficulty: Hard\nRecommended Characters: Dwarves, Noldor\nRegions: Moria, Misty Mountains",
campMirkwood = "Journey through Mirkwood",
campMirkwoodInfo = "You are to deliver an urgent message from King Thranduil to Queen Galadriel. Your journey will take you through Mirkwood, where darkness has been spreading lately.\n\nDifficulty: Easy\nRecommended Characters: Wood Elves\nRegion: Mirkwood",
campOldFord = "Journey up the Anduin",
campOldFordInfo = "After escorting Gandalf to Lothlórien, where Gollum is to be interrogated, you and your companions travel north along the Anduin to return to Beorn's Hall. You intend to cross the river at the Old Ford, which is guarded by the Beornings. Along the way you'll pass some small settlements of the Woodmen. Danger looms when you spot a Warg rider on a nearby hill. A scout perhaps?\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Any\nRegion: Anduin",
campOsgiliath = "Battle for Osgiliath",
campOsgiliathInfo = "After the battle for Cair Andros and the subsequent hunt for the scattered enemies inland, you return to Minas Tirith, where a lavish festival is celebrated to celebrate the victory. But the next morning, before you have slept off the intoxication, leave the governor will wake you up. A messenger has arrived with an urgent message: the enemy is moving against Osgiliath with another force and will reach the city in a few days.\n\nDifficulty: Hard\nRecommended characters: Gondor\nRegion: Osgiliath",
campOstmark = "Shield of the Ostfold",
campOstmarkInfo = "You have just entered the service of Rohan and have sworn your oath to the king to protect the land from his enemies, when bad news arrives in Edoras. Orcs have roamed the wasteland and invaded the Ostmark, the border guards were overrun and villages are on fire. King Théoden immediately assembles a band of horsemen and orders you to help defend the East March.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended characters: Rohan\nRegion: Rohan",
campRedhornGate = "The Redhorn Gate",
campRedhornGateInfo = "Celeborn has asked you to accompany Arwen, who is planning to visit her father in Rivendell. Your path will take you across the Redhorn Gate, which has many dangers lurking.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Noldor\nRegions: Misty Mountains, Rothorn Gate",
campRivendell = "The Road to Rivendell",
campRivendellInfo = "Your party has crossed the Rothorn Gate. Now you must head north and take the road along the Misty Mountains to Rivendell to bring Arwen home.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Noldor, Dúnedain\nRegions: Misty Mountains",
campThaudir = "The Dead Rise",
campThaudirInfo = "After storming the orc camp in the Weather Hills, you found the corpses of several men and women, believed to have been sacrificed in some malicious ritual, as well as a few confused survivors. This increases the Dúnedain's concern at the already strange actions of the orcs. After brief discussion, you decide to go with the Dúnedain and the survivors to Fornost Erain, where a grand gathering of rangers is taking place to celebrate the autumnal equinox.\n\nDifficulty: Hard\nRecommended Characters: Dúnedain\nRegion: Fornost",
campThreeClans = "Shadows over Dunland",
campThreeClansInfo = "After ending the Blood Pact, you receive an unexpected invitation to Isengard, where Saruman the White awaits you. In his wisdom, he expresses concern over the unrest in the wild lands of the Dunlendings. Saruman has a sinister suspicion: a dark force, about which Saruman remains vague, might be stirring up and manipulating the clans. You must uncover and neutralize this threat before it grows into a fire that endangers the peace of Middle-earth. To achieve this, you must pacify the quarrelsome clans of the Dunlendings and settle their old disputes. Your journey will take you to the edges of the known, where old secrets and new dangers await.\n\nDifficulty = Hard\nRecommended Characters = Rohirrim\nRegion = Dunland",
campVictory = "You won by fulfilling the campaign victory condition.",
campWatcher = "The watcher in the water",
campWatcherInfo = "You have successfully escorted Arwen to Rivendell. Elrond has asked you to scout the mines of Moria upon your return to Lórien to see if they are the source of the increased orc activity of recent times.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Noldor, Dwarves\nRegions: Eriador, Misty Mountains",
campWolfWastes = "The Wastes of Eriador",
campWolfWastesInfo = "The Battle of Fornost was fierce and bitter. Without the help of the heroes, the Dúnedain would probably have had to retreat. Ultimately, they suffered many wounds, but managed to repel the undead and imprison them in the undercity. But the evil spirit that suspected of raising the undead, managed to escape with some minions. What's more, one of the rangers claims to have seen them overpower Iâron and took him with them. After recent discoveries, you don't want to imagine his fate. While the Dúnedain need all the powers you need to secure the Dead Dike, you once again pursue the kidnappers as their trail leads northeast into the hilly wastelands of Eriador. Amarthiúl, a friend of Iâron, goes with you.\n\nDifficulty: Medium\nRecommended Characters: Dúnedain\nRegion: Eriador",
