localEventInfo = "COL_PHASE (local) COL_DEF ",
locBalrogText = "You are the father of our Folk, and we have bled for you and will again. But we will not enter Khazad-dum. Only I have looked through the shadow of the gate. Beyond the shadow it waits for you still: Durin's Bane. The world must change and some other power than ours must come before Durin's Folk walk again in Moria. – Dáin Ironfoot",
locDefScenarioGoal = "This is a custom scenario. Kill all enemies and resolve all objectives to win.",
locDolGuldurOrcsText = "Your path takes you and your companions close to Dol Guldur, the dark fortress in southern Mirkwood. There have long been rumors that something sinister has settled here and is slowly putting out feelers...",
locFordOfIsenText = "Bad things have been happening in Isengard lately. Saruman the White is no longer friend and protector of Isengard. White-handed Uruk-hai gather at the Fords of Isen and attempt to enter the Gates of Rohan. It's up to you and your companions to stop them for now.",
locGaladriel = "The mirror's vision",
locGaladrielGoal = "Kill all enemies and resolve all objectives to win.",
locGaladrielShort = "'Many things I can command the mirror to reveal... and some I can show what they desire to see. But the mirror will also show things not asked for, and these are often stranger and more useful than those things we wish to see. I can't say what you will see if you let the mirror work freely. For he shows things that were and things that are and things that may yet be, but what he now sees even the wisest do not always know. Would you like to look inside?'",
locGaladrielText = "Many things I can command the mirror to reveal... and some I can show what they desire to see. But the mirror will also show things not asked for, and these are often stranger and more useful than those things we wish to see. I can't say what you will see if you let the mirror work freely. For he shows things that were and things that are and things that may yet be, but what he now sees even the wisest do not always know. would you like to look inside",
locGraveText = "Once upon a time, the kings of the ancient kingdom of Arnor were buried in the Barrow Downs. But after the Great Plague in 1637 D.Z. grave fiends in the area. Recently, one hears again and again about missing travelers. So you and your companions decide to make the area a little safer again.",
locMarshText = "You could have wished for better weather, but it wasn't to be. Now the bugs come out of their den and make life difficult for you and your companions.",
locRhudaurText = "In these dark times, when darkness awakens anew, it is the duty of the Dúnedain to protect the few settlements to the north-east of Eriador. Between the Wetterberge, the Ettenmoors and the Misty Mountains lies the land of Rhudaur. Something evil has stirred up its crazed residents. They attack merchants and travelers more and more frequently. So you set out with your companions to patrol the Great East Road.",
locSnailText = "You force your battered body to straighten up while your head feels like you've had a midget feast. Your clothes are soaked with the stagnant water you lay in. Where did you get into here? And that shadow…did it just move? No, it's not a shadow, but a gigantic slug. She stretches her huge head and eye stalks in your direction and seems to have made up her mind. you are food.",
locTrollText = "On your way through the mountains you meet three fearsome trolls who immediately start talking about how best to cook you.",
locUngoliantText = "On the way through Mirkwood you and your companions are surprised by hideous spiders. They are powered by a monstrous matron descended directly from Ungoliant himself.",
loweredThreatBy1 = " has reduced COL_THREAT Threat COL_DEF by COL_THREAT ",
loweredThreatBy2 = "COL_DEF.",
makeFleeting = "Grant Fleeting",
manualSettings = "Custom Difficulty",
missionAnduin1 = "To the river!",
missionAnduin1Goal = "Get onto the raft and untie the ropes to continue your journey.",
missionAnduin1Info = "Still carrying a message from King Thranduil to Lady Galadriel, you leave Mirkwood with your companions. Your plan to raft south along the Anduin River is thwarted. When you reach the raft's dock, ask a giant hill troll gets in your way and you hear the shouts of orcs all around you.",
missionAnduin2 = "Ride the Anduin",
missionAnduin2Goal = "Clear all hazards to continue your journey.",
missionAnduin2Info = "Although you managed to outrun your enemies on the raft, navigating the wild river is anything but easy. Rapids and whirlpools have to be avoided, and your enemies have given chase along the bank.",
missionAnduin3 = "Ambush on the bank",
missionAnduin3Goal = "Defeat every enemy.",
missionAnduin3Info = "On the river you are too easy a target for the orcs' arrows. So you finally decide to go ashore. But the orcs are already waiting on both banks of the Anduin and you have no choice but to make your way to Lórien to fight through their ambush.",
missionAruwethil1 = "The hunt begins",
missionAruwethil1Count = " Enemies killed",
missionAruwethil1Goal = "Defeat 6 enemies per player or defeat every enemy in play to continue your journey before Arúwethil escapes.",
missionAruwethil1Info = "You stopped the miner's ritual and destroyed the horrible contraption. But the mysterious woman must still be somewhere. Nearby you see a staircase that leads down into the depths. You sense the danger the woman poses, and resolves with your companions to track them down in the city beneath Fornost's ruins and destroy them. May the hunt begin!",
missionAruwethil2 = "Flooded Vault",
missionAruwethil2Goal = "Defeat each enemy to continue your journey before Arúwethil escapes.",
missionAruwethil2Info = "You can sense the evil woman's presence in some way, letting you know you're on the right path. The Hillmen seem to have given up the pursuit. Your hunt takes you even deeper underground into a chamber that is partially flooded with stagnant water. Something seems to be moving inside…",
missionAruwethil3 = "Cornered",
missionAruwethil3Goal = "Defeat Arúwethil.",
missionAruwethil3Info = "As you begin to wonder where this hunt is going next, you realize that the corridor you are in now ends in a single chamber. It's time to end the hunt. Enter prepared you leave the room and there she stands, horrible and vicious. And filled with so much anger that you wonder if confrontation was a good idea. Suddenly she lets out a high-pitched scream and lunges at you, while the shadows seem to be moving.",
missionBarrowDowns1 = "Barrow Downs Trail",
missionBarrowDowns1Goal = "Search the camp for clues to continue your journey.",
missionBarrowDowns1Info = "Your research has revealed that the riot in Bree was part of a larger plan. You are determined to uncover it. At dawn you and your party follow a fresh lead into the Barrow Downs. A damp chill fills the air and it is strange silent. The flat hills in front of you are covered in dense fog. Suddenly screams reach your ears from there. They sound like men in panic. You immediately follow the screams and finally come across a devastated camp. In the fog you see some figures running wild, grapple with unseen opponents, or cower on the ground in fear. A pale man appears in front of you, glassy-eyed, gestures at your party. \"Here are more!\" he yells. More men appear and attack.",
missionBarrowDowns2 = "Disrupted Peace of the Dead",
missionBarrowDowns2Goal = "Resolve all hazards to continue your journey.",
missionBarrowDowns2Info = "You find out that the bandits are searching for rare items on behalf of a certain Denwyn. Apparently they had not realized the consequences of disturbing the peace of the dead in the Barrow Downs. In search of the remaining grave robbers and their leader, you go into the opened barrow.",
missionBarrowDowns3 = "Crypt of Cardolan",
missionBarrowDowns3Goal = "Clean up the tombs and defeat every villain.",
missionBarrowDowns3Info = "Not even the leader of the grave robbers seemed to have known what he was getting himself into. When you find him, you realize that he and his men have fallen victim to the grave fiends. Accompanied by a strange chant, they haunt three stone tombs, which seem to have gone into disarray. You wonder what will happen if you restore them.",
missionBreeMurder1 = "Search for the killer",
missionBreeMurder1Goal = "Investigate the clues in the inn and on the road to track the killer.",
missionBreeMurder1Info = "There had been a murder at the Prancing Pony Inn. Rat was new in town and had a thriving trade in things he said he'd found on his travels. But Barleyman was suspicious, and Rat was constantly looking around nervously, as if he'd been on the run.\nWhen you offer your help, the Barleyman lists some well-known suspects: Hans Goblin-Finger, Old Oreye, Suzy the Spider, Todd the Troll, Wolfskin-Jup, and a man you just name the orc. You promise to investigate the crime scene and catch the killer.",
missionBreeMurder2 = "More Questions",
missionBreeMurder2Goal = "Investigate the two locations to gather more clues and reveal the killer.",
missionBreeMurder2Info = "With the first clues, you can already rule out some of the suspects, but you still don't have enough information to accuse anyone. But the clues lead you to two places to investigate further. Just don't think that you leave the killer's henchmen alone.",
missionBreeMurder3 = "Confront the Murderer",
missionBreeMurder3Goal = "Defeat the villains responsible for the murder.",
missionBreeMurder3Info = "The pieces of the puzzle are beginning to fall together. You now know who must have committed the murder. And you've learned that an old acquaintance must somehow have had a hand in this: Lutz Farning. It's time to put the murderers to rest and hand them over to the villagers' justice.",
missionBreeTrouble1 = "Arrival in Bree",
missionBreeTrouble1Goal = "Defeat all enemies to continue your journey.",
missionBreeTrouble1Info = "After a long journey you have arrived in Bree. But it is the middle of the night and you only find closed shutters. As you wander through the streets, hooded figures suddenly appear from the shadows of the houses. Apparently the street thieves are stopping you and your companions for easy prey.",
missionBreeTrouble2 = "Hunt for artifacts",
missionBreeTrouble2Goal = "Collect 5 artifacts on players' hands to return to Lutz.",
missionBreeTrouble2Info = "When you routed the bandits, a guy comes up to you and thanks you for your help. He introduces himself as Lutz and reports that the bandits have been stealing from the villagers for a while. Apparently they had it particularly on unusual items. He promises you a reward if you manage to get the rare loot.",
missionBreeTrouble3 = "Bree Fight",
missionBreeTrouble3Goal = "Return all artifacts. You win when there are no artifacts left in a player's hand.",
missionBreeTrouble3Info = "You've done it and brought back the rare artifacts. Now you're off to the Prancing Pony Inn, where Lutz wanted to meet you. You can already hear loud shouting and banging from outside. When you come in, there's a real bar fight in the Underway. You must make your way through to bring the loot to Lutz.",
missionCairAndros1 = "Reinforcement for Cair Andros",
missionCairAndros1Goal = "Defend the riverbank.",
missionCairAndros1Info = "As soon as the news of the siege of Cair Andros had reached you, you and your companions set off to rush to the aid of the defenders of Gondor. When you arrive, an army of Orcs and Southrons is encamped on the east bank. Arrived under cover of night go to the island in small boats and prepare for battle. The enemies will mainly attack from the bridge and rafts across the river. The shore must not fall into their hands!\nThe sun will not rise in the morning. Blacks Clouds darken the sky and the assault on Cair Andros begins...",
missionCairAndros2 = "Storm on the Bridge",
missionCairAndros2Goal = "Defend the bridge.",
missionCairAndros2Info = "The attack across the river has been fended off for the time being. A messenger is already rushing towards you, requesting your support at the bridge. The enemy troops have already crossed the river and are now attacking the adjoining gate of the outer wall with battering rams.",
missionCairAndros3 = "The Final Rush",
missionCairAndros3Goal = "Defend the citadel and defeat every opponent",
missionCairAndros3Info = "You have successfully fended off the previous attacks. But unnoticed by the defenders, your enemies were able to land on rafts in the northern part of the island. There the citadel rises over the cliffs, on which the Anduin river breaks foaming. The attackers' superiority is mighty, but the stronghold of Gondor must stand firm at all costs!",
missionCarnDum1 = "Battle for Carn Dûm",
missionCarnDum1Goal = "Fight your way inside Carn Dûm while the battle is ongoing.",
missionCarnDum1Info = "The Dúnedain of the North and the Elves of Rivendell join forces to send a small army against the ruined fortress of Carn Dûm. Uncertain of what evil they will encounter, they are determined to put a stop to Angmar's awakening and the sending corrupted enemies back where they came from. It may be a tough fight, but the freedom of Eriador is at stake.",
missionCarnDum2 = "The Labyrinth of Despair",
missionCarnDum2Goal = "Find a way out of the Labyrinth of Despair.",
missionCarnDum2Info = "Amidst the turmoil of the siege, you and your party manage to fight a way inside the ruined fortress. Beneath the menacing towers of Carn Dûm, you enter an eerie system of tunnels and corridors whose inhabitants are not friendly to you You must get to the heart of evil, but you won't be let there without a fight.\nThe maze turns out to be extremely treacherous, and once you think you've found the exit, you'll find yourself back where you started your senses and drives you to despair. You must not give up, after all there has to be an exit somewhere...",
missionCarnDum3 = "The Source of Corruption",
missionCarnDum3Goal = "Destroy the Altar",
missionCarnDum3Info = "With horror and distress you have overcome the labyrinth and now venture into the heart of Carn Dûm. After you have defeated several guards, you reach a chamber with a strange altar. In front of it rises a figure that looks like one of the rangers looks, but her eyes are cold and her skin is sallow. She grasps a large longsword in both hands. At the same moment, you hear a whinny and an old acquaintance, in full battle armor, rides into the chamber on a great warhorse. Is this the opportunity, Thaurdir once and for all? Perhaps if you destroy this altar, you can defeat evil.",
missionCarrock1 = "Caught in the Storm",
missionCarrock1Goal = "Clear every hazard to continue your journey.",
missionCarrock1Info = "Two days ago you left Rivendell with your group of traveling companions to visit Beorn on the other side of the Misty Mountains. Now, wintry weather has surprised you. As you fight your way through the snow, orcs and wolves scent the area fresh loot.",
missionCarrock2 = "A restless night",
missionCarrock2Goal = "Survive the night to continue your journey.",
missionCarrock2Info = "You may have survived the worst of the snowstorms. But now the sun has set and the goblins are crawling out of their tunnels and caves in greater numbers. If you want to live in the morning, you can't afford a deep nap.",
missionCarrock3 = "Escape to Carrock",
missionCarrock3Goal = "Get across the river to shake off your pursuers for good.",
missionCarrock3Info = "You survived the night and got up at first light to leave the Misty Mountains behind you. But you are unlucky: the sky remains overcast and your enemies pursue you. You remember the rocky island of Carrock in the Middle of the Anduin. If you can make it there, you may have peace of mind from the orcs and their vile wargs.",
missionChetwald1 = "Intruders in Chetwood",
missionChetwald1Goal = "Stop the Orcs and defeat every Orc in play.",
missionChetwald1Info = "The Dúnedain of the Chetwood greet you with delight. They report that the orcs have already entered the forest, while others roam near the villages north of the forest. It is the ranger's self-imposed duty to keep the peaceful regions of Eriador free from any rabble. But with such an unusually large number of orcs, they won't refuse your help.\n'These orcs aren't roving goblins from the mountains.They are well equipped and definitely up to no good. No one knows what they're into this far struck the west, but we must stop them at all costs before they reach Bree.' So you get ready to fight.",
missionChetwald2 = "Tracking the Orcs",
missionChetwald2Goal = "Defeat all Orcs in play before they escape.",
missionChetwald2Info = "It was a hard fight, but hopefully the orcs have learned the lesson that they have no business being near settlements west of the Weather Hills. But the danger is not over yet. The orcs had split up and some groups moved still about the area. A Dúnedain scout reports that they were regrouping and marching towards the Weather Hills. 'They have taken prisoners in a little hamlet. Orcs don't normally take prisoners. Who knows where they're taking them?'",
missionChetwald3 = "Attack in the Weather Hills",
missionChetwald3Goal = "Fend off the orc counterattack by resolving every quest and defeating every Orc.",
missionChetwald3Info = "The pursuit of the orcs has taken you into the Weather Hills, known for their harsh, changeable weather. After slaying the last orc, you tend to the freed prisoners. What did the orcs want with them?\n\nAs you rest beneath a ruin of old Arnor, one of your friends who had been scouting the area suddenly rushes over: 'There are many more of them! They have a camp in the ruined castle there. I'm afraid they've already spotted us!'\nBefore you can answer, angry screams erupt from all directions. You stand up, draw your weapons and brace yourself.",
missionDolGuldur1 = "Into Dol Guldur",
missionDolGuldur1Goal = "Find a way into the fortress.",
missionDolGuldur1Info = "After your journey through Mirkwood, one thing is certain: dark things are happening around the old fortress of Dol Guldur. After some deliberation, Lady Galadriel asks you to investigate the dark fortress and find out what or who is up to mischief there.\nBut getting into the fortress isn't easy. Orcs and other creatures roam about. Galadriel told you about a hidden entrance at the bottom of the hill, but she couldn't tell exactly where it is.",
missionDolGuldur2 = "Lost under Dol Guldur",
missionDolGuldur2Goal = "Defeat the giant snail to continue on your way.",
missionDolGuldur2Info = "Although you and your companions have managed to find a way into the old fortress of Dol Guldur, trying to avoid the orcs you get lost in the underground tunnels and caves. Eventually you get into one kind of grotto with pale light and the smell of stale water. As you look around, something moves in the shadows. Two greenish lights appear and stare at you. They are the stalked eyes of a gigantic slug. It has recognized you and seems to have come to a decision to be.\nYou are food.",
missionDolGuldur3 = "Trap",
missionDolGuldur3Goal = "Close and barricade the door through which the orcs are pouring in.",
missionDolGuldur3Info = "Once the giant snail was struck down, you hurry to get out of the cave system. You find a staircase and run straight into the arms of an orc patrol. You can overpower them, but one of the orcs manages to escape and sound the alarm. A moment later, the alarm sounds shouts and drumbeats all around you. You desperately search for a way out, but the orcs are coming from all sides. You are surrounded.",
missionDruadan1 = "To the Drúadan Forest",
missionDruadan1Goal = "Resolve all quests to continue your journey.",
missionDruadan1Info = "After the costly but successful defense of Cair Andros, she follows a fleeing band of Orcs as they move westward into Gondor's interior. You must stop them before they can invade the hinterlands. But when their trail finally leads into the Drúadan- forest leads you into doubts...",
missionDruadan2 = "The Drúedain",
missionDruadan2Goal = "Convince the Drúedain that you are not enemies.",
missionDruadan2Info = "You scour the forest and slay one or two scattered orcs, but there is no sign of the flock you are pursuing. Suddenly a huge giant steps out from between the trees. More deformed-looking men crowd around him. Apparently you have trespassed on Drúedain territory, also known as Wasa or Pucklemen. Without their help you may never find your way out of this forest.\nBut first they will attack you.",
missionDruadan3 = "Save the innocent",
missionDruadan3Goal = "Save the villagers and prevent too many of them from being killed.",
missionDruadan3Info = "With a lot of effort you can teach the Drúedain that you don't want to fight them and that you will leave their lands as soon as you know where the orcs have gone. As it turns out, the Drúedain got you with your Enemies confused. Without further ado, they show you the path out of the forest that the orcs have taken. With a shock you realize that it leads directly to an unprotected village near the beacon mountain Amon Dîn. The villagers are defenseless at the mercy of the orcs.",
missionDunlandperlen1 = "The Captured Merchant",
missionDunlandperlen1Goal = "Rescue the merchant from captivity",
missionDunlandperlen1Info = "On your journey from Rohan to Rivendell, you come across the desperate wife of a merchant who pleads for the return of her husband. The Dunlanders have captured him, and he is in great danger. You decide to help and rescue him from the cruel Dunlanders. As you track down the Dunlanders, you realize that this will not be an easy task. The Dunlanders have the merchant bound, and the guards are numerous, but you know that the merchant has no chance if you do not act swiftly.",
missionDunlandperlen2 = "The Pearls of Love",
missionDunlandperlen2Goal = "Find the pearl necklace and retrieve it",
missionDunlandperlen2Info = "After rescuing the merchant, he tells you about a precious pearl necklace he had bought for his wife. The Dunlanders have stolen it and taken it to their village. This necklace means everything to him, and he implores you to retrieve it. So, you set out once more, this time to infiltrate the Dunlanders' village where the necklace is hidden. The danger is great, as the Dunlanders are on high alert, but you know you must recover the jewel to reunite the merchant with his wife.",
missionDunlandperlen3 = "Dunland on Your Heels",
missionDunlandperlen3Goal = "Shake off the pursuers and exhaust every Enemy",
missionDunlandperlen3Info = "The Dunlanders are enraged and have called for a hunt. With the merchant by your side and the precious necklace in your hands, you flee through the wild and unforgiving landscape. The Dunlanders are hot on your trail, and the escape becomes a race for your lives. The paths are treacherous and the terrain harsh, but you must reach safety before the Dunlanders catch up. The merchant's freedom and your own survival hang by a thread.",
missionDunlandwolves1 = "The Gates of Rohan",
missionDunlandwolves1Goal = "Defend the Fords and defeat every Eenemy.",
missionDunlandwolves1Info = "The Wolf Clan of the Dunlendings has mobilized its forces and is attacking the Fords of Isen in waves. These Fords are a strategically vital defense line for Rohan. Should the Dunlendings break through, the way into Rohan will be left unguarded. You must face the attackers, hold every position, and repel the enemy until the threat is eliminated. This defense is critical to stopping the advance of the Wolf Clan.",
missionDunlandwolves2 = "The Howling of Dunland",
missionDunlandwolves2Goal = "Follow the trail into the mountains and keep the Dunlendings in sight.",
missionDunlandwolves2Info = "You have successfully defended the Fords of Isen and shown the Dunlendings that Rohan is forbidden ground for them. But the blood pact between men and wolves is too great a threat to leave unchallenged. You must follow the trail of the Wolf Warriors back to Dunland and break the forbidden alliance with the Wargs. The hope of Rohan's people rests on your shoulders.",
missionDunlandwolves3 = "Breaking the Blood Pact",
missionDunlandwolves3Goal = "Find the sacrificial site of the blood pact, destroy it, and defeat every enemy.",
missionDunlandwolves3Info = "Through the interrogation of captured Dunlendings, you learn of an ancient sacrificial site deep in the mountains where the Wolf Clan seals its blood pact with the Wargs through the sacrifice of innocents. To end this threat, you must reach and destroy the sacrificial site. The path leads over an abandoned mountain road blocked by debris. As you clear the way, you will be constantly attacked by Dunlendings. You must reach the site at all costs and break the vile pact, even if it draws the wrath of the Wargs upon you. The success of this mission will determine the fate of Rohan.",
missionDurinsBane1 = "The Mines of Moria",
missionDurinsBane1Goal = "Defeat every enemy and solve every threat up to continue on your way.",
missionDurinsBane1Info = "You have ventured into the eastern mines of Moria. Along the way you will discover vast deposits of mithril - the only ones in all of Middle-earth - once mined by dwarves and now plundered by orcs.",
missionDurinsBane2 = "Shadow and Flame",
missionDurinsBane2Goal = "Escape the Balrog to get out of Moria.",
missionDurinsBane2Info = "You advance further and further to the east and the orcs you encounter become fewer. Hope is already burgeoning. Then you suddenly see a fiery glow in the darkness at the next archway. Then a being appears that is both fire and shadow seems to be. Can it be true? Is this Durin's curse, the cause of the fall of the dwarven empire of Khazad-dûm? One thing should be clear: this opponent is too strong for you.",
missionDurinsBane3 = "Flight to Lórien",
missionDurinsBane3Goal = "Defeat every enemy to complete the campaign.",
missionDurinsBane3Info = "You have wrestled with shadow and flame and somehow managed to escape the mines. Now you know what lurks in the terrible depths of Moria. Unfortunately, the sun is not in the sky right now. Orcs guard the east gate and become the pursuit You must route them once and for all and flee to Lórien.",
missionEdoras1 = "Edoras in Turmoil",
missionEdoras1Count = " Clues found",
missionEdoras1Goal = "Gather clues about the thieves. You are not allowed to play weapons in this location and you lose once Sauron's row is full.",
missionEdoras1Info = "You have just arrived in Edoras to offer your services to the king of Rohan when a riot breaks out in the city. Apparently the armory has been broken into and among the stolen weapons is said to be the royal sword Herugrim. No one would trust a local to commit such a brazen crime, so suspicion falls on you. You could not have arrived at a worse time, but at least the king is not convinced of your guilt. To save your own skin, you promise to by to help solve the theft. Your weapons will remain confiscated while you are in Edoras.",
missionEdoras2 = "Tracking the Thieves",
missionEdoras2Goal = "Follow the thieves' tracks to their lair. Alcaron must survive.",
missionEdoras2Info = "You get the crucial clue to the thieves from a guest from Gondor, who introduces himself as Alcaron. But when you break open the house of criminals, the thieves have already fled headlong.\nKing Théoden gives you the opportunity to restore your honor by retrieving the stolen weapons. However, to appease the townspeople, one of your companions must remain as a hostage while you and Alcaron follow the trail of the escaped bandits.",
missionEdoras3 = "Trapped in the Thieves' Den",
missionEdoras3Goal = "Defeat every enemy and recover Herugrim.",
missionEdoras3Info = "Without Alcaron, the thieves would probably have escaped. He leads you unerringly in the right direction and again and again you come across isolated bandits who stand in your way. When you reach a larger group of trees, numerous armed men suddenly jump between them trees and surround you. Then you hear Alcaron's laughter. 'Kill these simpletons and the weapons are ours,' he calls out to the bandits and draws his knife.",
missionErebor1 = "The Ancestral Forge",
missionErebor1Count = " Components needed to repair the forge",
missionErebor1Goal = "Repair the forge. Gather all components to avoid damage during the repair.",
missionErebor1Info = "The ancient halls of Erebor's forge have been cold for centuries, but reigniting its fire could herald a new golden age of dwarven craftsmanship. To restore the forge, you must find the scattered components and bring them back to the central smelter. Yet the tunnels are not unguarded – dangerous creatures of the dark lurk in the shadows. Only with courage and wit will you navigate these ancient halls and reignite the heart of the forge.",
missionErebor2 = "The City Under the Mountain",
missionErebor2Goal = "Clear the tunnel and resolve all Quests.",
missionErebor2Info = "After repairing the forge, your expedition ventures deeper into the darkened tunnels, long untouched by dwarven feet. Further into the mountain, you discover a vast network of passages infested with gruesome creatures. Their lairs span wide sections of the tunnels, threatening the safety of the forge. Your mission is to eliminate the infestation and secure the tunnels for future expeditions. But beware – the swarms hide in the darkness, and one wrong move could trigger a cascade of claws and fangs.",
missionErebor3 = "The Roots of Erebor",
missionErebor3Goal = "Secure the depths by resolving all Quests and defeating all Enemies.",
missionErebor3Info = "The expedition finally leads you to the deepest, unexplored chambers of Erebor, beyond the known tunnels and halls. No one has ever ventured this far down, and the dwarves do not know what lies in wait. However, strange sounds and missing workers point to a lurking threat in the dark. Your task is to explore and secure these regions, paving the way for the dwarves' expansion. Whatever you encounter below must be overcome, so Erebor can flourish in safety.",
missionEscapeDolGuldur1 = "In the Torture Chamber",
missionEscapeDolGuldur1Goal = "Free yourself from the chains and defeat the torturer to escape from the torture chamber.",
missionEscapeDolGuldur1Info = "While inspecting the dark fortress of Dol Guldur, your group has been captured and thrown into a prison deep underground. There, a cruel torturer will take care of your fate. If you don't want this to be your end, you must escape somehow and break free from the chains.",
missionEscapeDolGuldur2 = "The Source of Evil",
missionEscapeDolGuldur2Goal = "Defeat each enemy to continue your escape.",
missionEscapeDolGuldur2Info = "You managed to escape from the torture chamber. But you have no idea where it comes back to light. So you stumble through underground passages and finally find yourself in a large room lit by a bluish light. You hear words you do not understand - presumably it is the language of Mordor. So this is the source of the evil spreading from Dol Guldur. This necromancer can be none other than Sauron and you have run straight into his loyal servant.",
missionEscapeDolGuldur3 = "Dungeon Escape",
missionEscapeDolGuldur3Goal = "Find a way out of the caverns and the maze and defeat any villain who stands in your way.",
missionEscapeDolGuldur3Info = "You have defeated the necromancer's servant and are now desperately looking for an exit from the dark fortress. You are lost in the endless caverns of the underground dungeon.",
missionEttenmoors1 = "The Old Bridge",
missionEttenmoors1Goal = "Cross the old bridge",
missionEttenmoors1Info = "You and your group have escaped from captivity in Mount Gram. Although you managed to shake off your pursuers, you now face the arduous journey through the wilderness of the Ettenmoors.\nAfter a long rest, in which you again Once you have regained some strength, you begin the march through the Ettenmoors. Your first obstacle is to cross the Greyspring. When you reach an ancient bridge, you are ambushed by the wild people of Rhudaur. You must get to the other side, before they surround you.",
missionEttenmoors2 = "Land of Trolls",
missionEttenmoors2Goal = "Resolve each Quest",
missionEttenmoors2Info = "You've crossed the Greyspring and the wildmen are left behind on the other side, apparently realizing that you're not easy prey. Or maybe they know the area and know that trolls roam here and it's best not to go in get into their quarrels…",
missionEttenmoors3 = "Time for dinner",
missionEttenmoors3Goal = "Defeat every Troll",
missionEttenmoors3Info = "Under the cover of night you try to sneak past the trolls, but they notice you. You are horrified when you notice the large cauldron over their campfire, which they have prepared especially for you. Now you have to come up with something to avoid going to the become troll fodder.",
missionFangorn1 = "Persecution in Fangorn",
missionFangorn1Count = " cards played by Sauron",
missionFangorn1Goal = "The pursuit is successful when Sauron has played a certain number of cards.",
missionFangorn1Info = "You pursue a group of fleeing orcs who have survived the battle in the wastelands. Driven by desperation, ignorance or sheer madness, they flee to Fangorn, of all places, the ancient forest on the border with Rohan. It may be foolhardy, but you cannot allow these orcs to plunder Rohan again. So you continue the pursuit in the forest.",
missionFangorn2 = "The Forest Аwakens",
missionFangorn2Goal = "Try to escape from Fangorn by solving every quest.",
missionFangorn2Info = "As you have hunted down some fleeing orcs and caught the last remnants, the shadows around you suddenly become thicker and strange noises arise. A deep hum, a threatening groan and an angry growl. The trees over there have just opened up moved?\n\nThe Huorns have awakened. They make no distinction between the forest invaders. Defeat a random Orc whenever a Huorn comes into play.",
missionFangorn3 = "The Heart of the Forest",
missionFangorn3Goal = "Call the Ents for help. Rowan and Haleth must survive.",
missionFangorn3Info = "The shadow of the forest becomes thicker and fear runs through your limbs. Soon you can barely see your hand in front of your eyes and flee blindly through the forest. Separated from your friends, you reach a clearing where you have an unexpected encounter: two female adventurers Rhovanion's forest people stand back to back surrounded by angry Huorns. You forget your escape and rush to their aid.\nBut a fight against the angry Huorns is hopeless. If you want to somehow escape from this darkest part of the forest, then you must call the tree shepherds to appease the wild trees.",
missionFornost1 = "On the Dead Dike",
missionFornost1Count = " Enemies defeated",
missionFornost1Goal = "Defeat 6 enemies per player or defeat every enemy in play or bring down the wall. Beravor must survive.",
missionFornost1Info = "In the notes of the grave robbers at the Barrow Riss you have found a hint that your actual client is in Fornost and is working on secret machinations there. So you go north on the road to Fornost Erain, in the Shire and from the Bree people also known as Dead Dike. Beravor, who knows the area like no other, is your guide. The ruins of Arnor's last capital seem to have come alive again. Hillmen have set up several camps. They won't let you in easily.",
missionFornost2 = "A Desperate Plan",
missionFornost2Goal = "Bring down the tower to thwart the ritual. Beravor must survive.",
missionFornost2Info = "Beravor leads you through the streets of Fornost as if she grew up there and as if the town were not a crumbling ruin. From an old watchtower you get an overview. You spy a large crowd of hillmen surrounding a darkly dressed woman. You can't understand her words as she fiddles with a strange contraption. You notice brown fumes rising from her. Whatever is going on, you must stop this witchcraft. Perhaps the tower can be brought down? He could bury the woman and her device.",
missionFornost3 = "Chaos Under the City",
missionFornost3Goal = "Find and destroy the device.",
missionFornost3Info = "After the tower collapsed, you wake up in a cloud of dust, coughing and rattling. All around you are hillmen, staring in shock. You all fell into a vast underground chamber that lay beneath the town.\nThen you hear the dark voice of the woman ordering the hillmen to search for the device and eliminate the intruders. You have to be faster.",
missionFoundation1 = "Lost in the Deep",
missionFoundation1Goal = "Follow the sound of the water to continue your journey.",
missionFoundation1Info = "You are lost in the depths of Moria fleeing the orcs. Not knowing which way leads back to the daylight, you follow the dull murmur of an underground river, hoping it will lead you to the exit.",
missionFoundation2 = "Washed Down",
missionFoundation2Goal = "Find your way around and clear all objectives to continue your journey.",
missionFoundation2Info = "You'll know you're walking in the right direction when the noise behind the walls gets louder and louder. Eventually it swells to a real roar as the corridors get narrower and narrower. When you knock on a wall as a test, rock crumbles from the ceiling and suddenly the floor crumbles away. You fall powerlessly into the torrent you've been following all along. When you come to, you're deeper than ever and all your gear is scattered around.",
missionFoundation3 = "Fight Free",
missionFoundation3Goal = "Defeat the goblin chief.",
missionFoundation3Info = "As if it weren't hard enough to find your way up in the disorientation, the orcs will become more and more numerous on your way. In a larger hall you finally see a huge orc who is gathering many smaller goblins around him. He must be a chief or something similar. The enemies might let you go if you kill their chief.",
missionFramsburg1 = "Gundabad Raiders",
missionFramsburg1Goal = "Defeat each enemy to continue your journey.",
missionFramsburg1Info = "You decide to recover the legendary sword Frams, which Fram used to slay the dragon Scatha, from the ruins of old Framsburg. When you arrive at the confluence of the Anduin headwaters Langwell and Greylin, you run into a troop of orcs. They are believed to be from Gundabad Mountain and are out for trouble, unfortunately for you.",
missionFramsburg2 = "The Ruins of Framsburg",
missionFramsburg2Goal = "Search the ruins until you find the entrance to Fram's crypt.",
missionFramsburg2Info = "You have shaken off the orcs and reached the city of Framsburg, abandoned for centuries. As you carefully climb the crumbling city walls, you find that it is not as deserted as you thought it is after all. Orcs roam in search of useful, and apparently they have awakened wights like those you know from the barrows. Finding Fram's sword is proving to be harder than you thought.",
missionFramsburg3 = "The Cursed Grave",
missionFramsburg3Goal = "Open the cursed tomb.",
missionFramsburg3Info = "You have finally found the entrance to a large crypt where Fram was laid to rest. But apparently he is much more restless than you would expect. As soon as you enter the crypt, you are surrounded by undead. 'Who disturbs the Quiet from Fram, Frumgar's son?' asks a grave-deep voice. You see a giant standing in front of the grave, armed with sword and shield. Perhaps it is true that the dwarves, when Fram refused to give them any of the dragon's treasure and instead only sent Scatha's teeth, cursing him and finally slaying him. It seems like if you want the sword, you will have to defeat the vengeful spirit.",
missionGollum1 = "On the Trail of Gollum",
missionGollum1Goal = "Find Gollum's trail inside the forest.",
missionGollum1Info = "You have agreed to help Gandalf in his search for the creature Gollum. The site of his sighting is at the edge of Mirkwood. The old wizard leads you into the forest and is confident that you will find a trail there. He suggests that you split up. 'In two groups we have a better chance of success', he said and had apparently decided to be one of these groups yourself. So you are now on your own...\nBut apparently you are not the only ones chasing Gollum. After a few steps you realize that orcs are nearby and the creatures of the forest seem to be in great turmoil. At least they are very aggressive.",
missionGollum2 = "Deeper into the forest",
missionGollum2Goal = "Follow Gollum's trail and defeat every spider.",
missionGollum2Info = "You have found a trace that may have come from Gollum. But you are not sure. You have now penetrated deep into southern Mirkwood, and when you allow yourself the luxury of a short rest, you are suddenly struck by this abominable Ambush Spiderspawn.",
missionGollum3 = "Gollum in Shackles",
missionGollum3Goal = "Free Gollum and prevent his escape.",
missionGollum3Info = "You've shaken off the pesky spiders and at the same time managed to follow Gollum's trail. You sneak quietly through the forest and come across an orc camp, presumably from a Dol Guldur patrol. In the middle of the camp you see a gaunt creature tied up on a thick tree trunk. Apparently the enemy had found Gollum first and might now be interrogating him in a dark dungeon. Even if you detest the creature, you cannot let that happen. But in order to free Gollum, you must drive the orcs out and secure them at the same time, that Gollum cannot escape in the rush of battle that ensues.",
missionGondorConspiracy1 = "A Request from the Steward",
missionGondorConspiracy1Goal = "Uncover the conspiracy in Minas Tirith.",
missionGondorConspiracy1Info = "At the invitation of the Steward of Gondor, you and your fellowship arrive in Minas Tirith, the White City. You learn that the governor is concerned about suspicious activity in the city. Gondor has enough enemies outside the city walls. He begs you to investigate the clues to a possible conspiracy.",
missionGondorConspiracy2 = "Into the sewage",
missionGondorConspiracy2Goal = "Defeat each enemy to get to the conspirators' lair.",
missionGondorConspiracy2Info = "It took some effort, but finally you can put all the pieces of the puzzle together. The picture that emerges is anything but pleasant: Apparently there is a ring of conspirators in the underground of Minas Tirith. The only thing you know about their leader so far is that he named himself after a former ruler of Gondor. And the way to his lair is through the city's sewers of all places.",
missionGondorConspiracy3 = "In the Nest of Criminals",
missionGondorConspiracy3Goal = "Defeat the villain leading the conspiracy ring.",
missionGondorConspiracy3Info = "You have braved the foul stench of the sewage and the hordes of annoying rats in the sewers and found the nest of the bandits. Your goal is clear: In order to bring peace to the city, the snake's head must be cut off.",
missionGram1 = "The dungeon of Mount Gram",
missionGram1Goal = "Rescue Iâron and leave the dungeon. Amarthiúl must survive. If you leave the dungeon and Iâron is not in play, the mission fails.",
missionGram1Info = "After fleeing the Wargs had drained you, the Orcs easily overwhelmed you. They took you tied up to Mount Gram, where they locked you in individual dungeons deep within the mountain.\n\nHours and days seemed like to pass away, but how many you could not say. Rarely would the cell be unlocked and foul-smelling meat brought to you, which you would eat only reluctantly. Occasionally you hear screams somewhere and hoped they were not those of your companions.\nWhen once again a keeper unlocked the door, the monotony and hopelessness had already caused you to indulge in dreary thoughts. You hardly noticed the shadow that slipped through the door behind the keeper. One quick movement and the orc sank to the ground, gurgling. 'Quickly,' Amarthiúl whispered as he unlocked your chains. 'Let's free the others before the alarm goes off.'",
missionGram2 = "Out of Mount Gram",
missionGram2Goal = "Escape from Mount Gram. Amarthiúl and Iâron must survive.",
missionGram2Info = "You were lucky in that your own arrest led to Iâron's release. But now the orcs have sounded the alarm and the way Amarthiúl got to the dungeon is blocked. So you have to get out in a hurry escape the dungeon. Since none of you know your way around here, you of all things stumble into a large chamber with all kinds of torture tools. A giant orc turned to you with a grunt, raised his muscular, log-thick arms and charged you.",
missionGram3 = "Not escaped yet",
missionGram3Goal = "Escape the pursuers by defeating every enemy. The mission fails if Sauron has a full row at the end of the round.",
missionGram3Info = "You managed to escape from the mountain, but your escape did not go unnoticed. Swarms of orcs swarm out and attach themselves to your heels. When a horrid howl sounds, you realize that the wargs have something in common with the orcs. Angry at your escape, they probably won't capture you again this time. You'd better kill them before they surround you.",
missionIthilien1 = "To Ithilien",
missionIthilien1Goal = "Find a way through Ithilien by you resolve all hazars.",
missionIthilien1Info = "After you have uncovered and eliminated the conspiracy in Minas Tirith, the steward informs you about the threat on the outer borders of the country. Corsairs threaten the south coast and drive through the Anduin estuary to Pelargir, orc squads are in the vicinity of Cair Andros has been seen to the north and Sauron's allies from the south are marching through Ithilien into Mordor.\nThe Steward hands you an important message to Celador, who commands the rangers in Ithilien in Faramir's absence.",
missionIthilien2 = "Mercenaries from the South",
missionIthilien2Goal = "Defeat each enemy to continue your journey.",
missionIthilien2Info = "Ithilien becomes more and more hostile the longer it suffers from Sauron's rule. You are making slow progress and have to wrestle with a lot of resistance. After you have taken a longer rest, you suddenly hear strange voices. They were not the usual orcs. The Stewardess's information was apparently correct: mercenaries from the south traveled to the Black Gate to enlist in Sauron's service. You must stop them.",
missionIthilien3 = "The Guardians of Ithilien",
missionIthilien3Goal = "Defeat every enemy from Harad and every rogue and defeat the southerners' reinforcements in the Escape.",
missionIthilien3Info = "When you've already dealt badly with the mercenaries, arrows suddenly whizz out of nowhere and strike down the remaining enemies. Shortly thereafter, some rangers emerge from between the trees, whose leader pretends to be Celador. After a short greeting, the men will lead you to Henneth Annûn, a secret base of the Rangers. From retreats like these, the men in the service of Gondor watch over Ithilien as best they can. There you deliver the Steward's message to Celador. In return, he tells you of a large company of Southrons, moving through Ithilien. They must not reach the Black Gate. The rangers are already preparing to ambush and are asking for your assistance.",
missionKidnapping1 = "A bad morning",
missionKidnapping1Goal = "Defeat each opponent to go in search of your companion.",
missionKidnapping1Info = "You are visiting Beorn and enjoying his courteous inn with your friends. In the morning after a night of drinking honey mead, however, you make a disturbing discovery: one of your companions has disappeared without a trace! What happened? Nobody noticed anything To top it all off, Beorn isn't home either. When you go to look for him in the beehives, you are attacked by panicked swarms of bees. Something must have incited them.",
missionKidnapping2 = "Kidnapped and Wrapped",
missionKidnapping2Goal = "Cut the cocoons and free your friend.",
missionKidnapping2Info = "After taming the bees, you notice a trail of downed grass leading east from Beorn's hall. You set out with your remaining companions to find your missing friend. The trail takes you to the edge of Mirkwood leads, you already suspect nothing good. And indeed: After fighting your way through dense undergrowth, you come to a nest of disgusting forest spiders. Several cocoons are hanging from the branches. Is your friend among them? One of the cocoons is wriggling wildly. It's best if you open them all.",
missionKidnapping3 = "Beating-up",
missionKidnapping3Goal = "Defeat the three big spiders.",
missionKidnapping3Info = "What a load falls from your heart when you free your friend alive from the disgusting cocoon. The reunion is warm, but it is suddenly interrupted. There are tremors and cracking in the undergrowth and suddenly three large spiders appear. As they see, they become angry that their prey has been freed. You've got the right opportunity. It's only fitting to teach the kidnappers a lesson.",
missionLongDark1 = "At the West Gate",
missionLongDark1Goal = "Open the gate to Moria to continue your journey.",
missionLongDark1Info = "You must enter the Mines of Moria to find out what is happening in the abandoned dwarf city. To do so, however, you must find the Doors of Durin, which are only visible by starlight and moonlight, and speak the correct password. To Don't wait too long, because the guardian in the water may be wounded, but certainly not defeated. The next few tentacles are already snaking out of the water…",
missionLongDark2 = "The Long Dark",
missionLongDark2Goal = "Resolve all hazards and enlight the darkness or your group is lost.",
missionLongDark2Info = "You've made it into Moria's interior. Unsure of what awaits you, you begin to explore the branched system of corridors and halls. It soon becomes clear: Without a light source, you won't survive the journey through the darkness in one piece.",
missionLongDark3 = "Surrounded!",
missionLongDark3Goal = "Repel the orc attack and defeat each enemy to complete the campaign.",
missionLongDark3Info = "The further East you go, the more Orcs you'll encounter. So far they've seemed disorganized, but your presence seems to be drawing more and more attention. Suddenly, thumping drums and shrieks ring out from the depths. More Orcs appear, and soon you're already surrounded. You might be able to make your way to the bridge at the east gate.",
missionMirkwood1 = "Blocked Path",
missionMirkwood1Goal = "Find a way past the spiders to continue the journey.",
missionMirkwood1Info = "You set out with an urgent message from King Thranduil to Lady Galadriel of Lórien. Your journey takes you deep into Mirkwood, where strange things have been happening lately. The further south you go, the darker it gets around you. Eventually, a thick dead tree trunk blocks the way. As you try to go around it, foul creatures attack you.",
missionMirkwood2 = "Caught in the web",
missionMirkwood2Goal = "Escape the spiders by destroying the wall of webs.",
missionMirkwood2Info = "Surprised by your aggressiveness, the spiders retreat for a brief moment. Your joy at having found a way past them is short-lived. After just a few steps, large spider webs block the way and the ugly creatures have surrounded you.",
missionMirkwood3 = "Ungoliant's Spawn",
missionMirkwood3Goal = "Defeat Ungoliant's spawn.",
missionMirkwood3Info = "You have just managed to cut a hole in the webs through which you can escape, when suddenly you are confronted with a massive creature - a spider, even bigger and uglier than the others. As she corners you, more spiders crawl out of their holes. It could be tough against all of them, but they might let you go if you kill the big spider.",
missionOldFord1 = "Up the Anduin",
missionOldFord1Goal = "Defend yourself against enemies as you travel up the Anduin.",
missionOldFord1Info = "You are on your way north from Lórien. The banks of the Anduin are densely forested and here and there small settlements of the woodmen dot the path. Your journey is peaceful until you spot a warg rider on a nearby hill? A scout? You must be on it be prepared for other orcs to be around.",
missionOldFord2 = "Woodmen under attack!",
missionOldFord2Goal = "Protect the village and repel the attack by killing every enemy.",
missionOldFord2Info = "As you get further north, you notice columns of smoke on the horizon. You hurry and see a woodmen village that is partially on fire. Soon you hear the sounds of battle. It happens again and again that the settlements are attacked by marauding orcs. But maybe you can help these villagers in time.",
missionOldFord3 = "The Old Ford",
missionOldFord3Goal = "Secure the Old Ford and defeat every enemy.",
missionOldFord3Info = "The villagers are extremely grateful for your help. Haldan, a tall woodsman, offers to escort you to the Old Ford. He wants to warn the Beornings of the growing danger of orc attacks. But when you arrive at the ford, you find yourself in the middle of a fight again. Orcs are trying to storm the Old Ford and so far they're being thrown back by the Beornings in a ferocious rage. But more are coming.",
missionOsgiliath1 = "Get ready for battle!",
missionOsgiliath1Goal = "Time is short, so make final preparations.",
missionOsgiliath1Info = "On the morning after a lavish feast in Gondor's capital, you receive an urgent message from Osgiliath. Rangers report a formidable force of Orcs and Haradrim marching against the river city, whose east bank is already under Mordor's control. War Cair Andros just a diversion? In any case, the enemy is stronger than expected. If you hurry, you'll get to Osgiliath before the army and you can do some battle preparations.",
missionOsgiliath2 = "Defend Osgiliath",
missionOsgiliath2Count = " … districts successfully defended.",
missionOsgiliath2Goal = "Defend the four quarters of Osgiliath one at a time.",
missionOsgiliath2Info = "In the time you had left, you did your best to prepare for the upcoming battle. As darkness falls, the attack begins. Sauron's forces attack Osgiliath across the board. You can't possibly be everywhere at the same time, but the Defenders anywhere will need your support to throw the enemy back.",
missionOsgiliath3 = "Reclaim the East Bank",
missionOsgiliath3Goal = "Free the East Bank.",
missionOsgiliath3Info = "Gondor's soldiers fight back bravely and the longer the night goes on, the weaker the enemy's onslaught. As morning approaches, you can drive them back across the river. Completely reclaim Gondor's former capital.",
missionOstmark1 = "The Ostfold is burning",
missionOstmark1Count = " Orcs played to defeat",
missionOstmark1Goal = "Resolve all Quests before Sauron plays enough Orcs to devaste the Ostfold",
missionOstmark1Info = "Bad news arrives in Edoras. Orcs have roamed the wasteland and invaded the Ostmark, the border guards have been overrun and villages are on fire. King Théoden immediately assembles a band of horsemen and orders you to defend the Ostfold to help.\n\nYou set out immediately to protect the threatened villages and stop the marauding orcs. But you can't be everywhere at once...",
missionOstmark2 = "Battle in the Wastes",
missionOstmark2Goal = "Fight your way to the captain.",
missionOstmark2Info = "You threw the marauding hordes out of the Ostfold and protected the villages for the moment. But messengers tell you that the orcs are massing in the wastelands and are forming a force to invade again in full force. The Rohirrim must move form up and ride out to strike down the enemy before he invades.",
missionOstmark3 = "In the Heart of the Horde",
missionOstmark3Goal = "Defeat all Orcs.",
missionOstmark3Info = "With your companions you have penetrated deep into the horde of orcs in the heat of battle and have reached the captain. This is your opportunity: the death of their leader could significantly weaken the orcs.",
missionRedhornGate1 = "Up the Dimrill Stairs",
missionRedhornGate1Goal = "Defeat each enemy and climb the Dimrill Stairs to get to the pass and continue your journey. Arven must survive.",
missionRedhornGate1Info = "Celeborn has asked you to accompany Arwen, who wants to visit her father in Rivendell. Your path leads you over the Redhorn Gate, where many dangers lurk. First you have to follow the deep cut path up to the pass in the Shadowriver Valley. As When you arrive at the torrent, you will notice a huge bear that immediately pounces on you.",
missionRedhornGate2 = "The Redhorn Gate",
missionRedhornGate2Goal = "Conquer the mountains to continue your journey. Arven must survive.",
missionRedhornGate2Info = "You have reached the Rothorn Gate and must fight your way through fierce gusts and snowdrifts. As the freezing cold gnaws at your limbs, you see goblins and wargs eyeing you keenly.",
missionRedhornGate3 = "They are waiting for you",
missionRedhornGate3Goal = "Defeat all enemies that in order to win. Arven must survive.",
missionRedhornGate3Info = "You've left the peaks of the mountains behind, but as you descend from the pass, goblins attack you, as if angry that you've survived the freezing cold this far.",
missionRivendell1 = "The Road to Rivendell",
missionRivendell1Goal = "Take the road to Rivendell, to continue your journey. Arwen must survive.",
missionRivendell1Info = "After crossing the Rothorn Gate, your party heads north. Your path now leads you along the foothills of the Misty Mountains and you soon find yourself being watched from the shadows.",
missionRivendell2 = "Crack in the Mountain",
missionRivendell2Goal = "Close the gates to push back the goblins and continue your journey. Arwen must survive.",
missionRivendell2Info = "Exhausted from your journey, you look for a place to stay for the night. But as soon as night falls, you are swarming with orcs. Apparently there is some kind of gate nearby that they use to get out of the mountains.",
missionRivendell3 = "Hunted!",
missionRivendell3Goal = "Defeat every enemy to reach Rivendell safely. Arwen must survive.",
missionRivendell3Info = "You managed to escape the goblins. But soon you realize that you are being followed. Angry at your escape, they sent the wargs to follow your trail. Rivendell is not far now, but it might be difficult to escape from the wargs.",
missionThaudir1 = "An Unpleasant Surprise",
missionThaudir1Goal = "Resolve the Quest to push back the undead",
missionThaudir1Info = "When you arrive at the Dúnedain in Fornost, you tell about the experiences with the orcs and the humans who have apparently become victims of a ritual. Aragorn wants to interview the survivors personally. But when they are brought to him, you notice that an elderly man is missing who hadn't spoken a word. Your friends can't tell you where he's gone. Suddenly a ranger comes running up. 'We've been tricked! They're attacking us!'\nAragorn straightens up immediately. 'Who's attacking? What's going on, Iâron?'\n'The old man and two of the survivors,' the ranger gasped, 'they are … ghosts.' Before anyone could reply, you hear the sounds of battle nearby. Aragorn draws his sword. Aragorn draws his sword. 'Follow me!', he calls, leading you into battle.",
missionThaudir2 = "The Shadows of Angmar",
missionThaudir2Goal = "Defeat all Undead before they overwhelm you",
missionThaudir2Info = "When the undead begun to rise up and attacked the Dúnedain in Fornost, you realized why the ancient capital of Arthedain is now called the Deadmen's Dike by the Bree-landers. Under Aragorn's leadership, you help the distressed rangers push back the restless dead. But you can only fight for a brief respite. More Dúnedain join you and report that the mindless dead have risen throughout Fornost. 'A dark sorcery has awakened them,' says one of the rangers. You gather with the others around Aragorn and stand in the way of the approaching dead.",
missionThaudir3 = "Gate of the Dead",
missionThaudir3Goal = "Close the Gate of the Dead and raise Fate Meter to it's maximum to defeat the dark sorcery and restore peace",
missionThaudir3Info = "The Dúnedain fought valiantly, and enemy after enemy was struck down. But where one falls, another rises. 'We must root out their origin,' proclaims Aragorn. 'The old man you brought here. Has anyone seen him?'\n'I think I saw him over there,' replied Iâron.\nYou fight your way in the indicated direction and indeed you see the old man, who had now completely transformed. Revealed in his true form, he stood before a black gate from which the undead of the Undercity poured. If you bring it down, you might be able to imprison the undead underground. But the old man, who has now become a terrifying spirit, will not let you there without a fight.",
missionThreeClans1 = "Three Trials",
missionThreeClans1Count = " Clan chiefs successfully challenged",
missionThreeClans1Goal = "Challenge and defeat the chieftains of the three clans to convince them",
missionThreeClans1Info = "Saruman gives you the task of pacifying the three powerful clans of the Dunlendings: the Wolf Clan, the Raven Clan, and the Boar Clan. Each of these clans is led by a proud chieftain who refuses to hear you out without a fight. You must seek out the clans and successfully challenge the chieftains to gain their respect and secure their loyalty. Only by passing these trials will you be able to unite the clans and overcome the first obstacle on your path to pacifying these wild lands. An unexpected help comes your way: the forest people Rowan and Haleth, whom you had freed from Fangorn, accompany you to Dunland.",
missionThreeClans2 = "The Guardians Rise",
missionThreeClans2Goal = "Gain access to the Ancient Burial Mound",
missionThreeClans2Info = "After your impressive display on the battlefield, the chieftains are ready to speak with you. You learn that a strange outsider has incited the clans. He is said to have taken refuge in an ancient burial mound on the great clan hill, where he only communicates with select messengers and issues orders. You set out to enter the burial mound, but upon your arrival, you are confronted by the powerful guardians of the clans, who have sworn to protect the tomb from intruders. To open the entrance and obtain the keys to the crypts, you must defeat these blood-sworn warriors and prove that your cause is just.",
missionThreeClans3 = "A Shadow in Dunland",
missionThreeClans3Goal = "Defeat Morcarach and seal the crypts",
missionThreeClans3Info = "As you enter the burial mound, the true threat reveals itself: Morcarach, the Shadow of Angmar, shows his face. This ancient enemy has stirred up the clans and seeks to cover the land in darkness to pave the way for a greater power. Now he raises the spirits of the clans from their crypts to destroy you. To fulfill Saruman's request, you must defeat Morcarach and seal the crypts of the clans with the keys to banish the corruption. The outcome of this final battle will determine the fate of Rohan and the Dunlendings; otherwise, Middle-earth will soon face a much greater darkness.",
missionWatcher1 = "Journey to Moria",
missionWatcher1Goal = "Clear the warg lairs to continue your journey.",
missionWatcher1Info = "Elrond of Rivendell has asked you to scout the mines of Moria on your return journey to Lórien to see if they are the source of the increased orc activity of recent times. Shortly after you left the safety of Rivendell, the wargs found yours taking the scent…",
missionWatcher2 = "At the west gate",
missionWatcher2Goal = "Defeat each enemy to continue your journey.",
missionWatcher2Info = "You have almost reached the West Gate of Moria. Blocking your way is a black lake, dammed by the Sirannon. Its waters are deep and suspiciously still. As you look around the lake, screams ring out and you are struck by Goblins attacked.",
missionWatcher3 = "The Watcher",
missionWatcher3Goal = "Defeat the watcher in the water.",
missionWatcher3Info = "You fight back bitterly and successfully. The goblins let go of you. You are just about to catch your breath when you hear a strange noise and the water of the lake suddenly seems to be moving. Suddenly, tentacles spring out of the lake and strike at your companions. You slam the tentacles wildly, but more keep coming. And then a nameless creature rises from the water.",
missionWolfWastes1 = "From Hunter to Hunted",
missionWolfWastes1Goal = "Survive the journey through the wilderness as night and day alternate. Amarthiúl must stay in play.",
missionWolfWastes1Info = "After the battle against the undead on the Dead Dike, the ranger Iâron was kidnapped by the spirit Thaurdir, who first appeared to you as an old man. Not willing to give him another cruel fate, you follow the trail of the kidnappers in the wastelands of Eriador. Amarthiúl, a friend of Iâron, goes with you.\n\nHowever, you quickly find that you cannot keep up with the speed of the enemies, who need neither sleep nor food.As you set up camp in the middle of the wilderness, you hear the howling for the first time. It seems to be coming from everywhere at once. Soon you realize that you seem to have gone from hunter to hunted. While the wolves are initially reluctant in daylight, they will pounce on you at night.",
missionWolfWastes2 = "Prepare the camp",
missionWolfWastes2Goal = "Prepare to fight the Pack",
missionWolfWastes2Info = "You have now advanced a good distance into the wastelands while fighting off the hungry wolves. However, as the number increases, you signal your companions to stop. You mean one in particular in the moonlight at night After seeing the big warg, you make a decision. You can't run any longer. If you're going to somehow survive the march across the wasteland, you'll have to get rid of the wolves once and for all. So while it's still day, you're attempting a fortified camp It is clear to all of you: as soon as night comes, the pack will attack you.",
missionWolfWastes3 = "Battle with the Pack",
missionWolfWastes3Goal = "Survive the attack and defeat every Enemy",
missionWolfWastes3Info = "As soon as the sun has dipped below the horizon, dozens of beastly throats emit a terrifying howl. And then, in the pale moonlight, a giant warg approaches. Your eyes were not deceiving you, this sinister creature appears to be the leader of the pack. You and your companions draw your weapons. May this be your last fight, let it be a heroic one.",
